nction_symbol.binary</a> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-t\">t</a></span></span></span></code></summary><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-binary\"><a href=\"#type-binary\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> binary</span><span> = <span><a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Function_symbol/index.html#type-binary\">Operator.Function_symbol.binary</a> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-boolean\"><a href=\"#type-boolean\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> boolean</span><span> = <span><a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Function_symbol/index.html#type-boolean\">Operator.Function_symbol.boolean</a> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-biadd\"><a href=\"#val-biadd\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> biadd : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">flags</span>:<a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Flags/Biadd/index.html#type-t\">Operator.Flags.Biadd.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector Integer ADDition. Operaters on bitvectors of size <code>size</code>. The flags represent behavior on overflow:</p><ul><li><code>nuw</code>: no unsigned wrap: the operation is partial, i.e. fails if the sum of the two operands (interpreted as unsigned numbers) is not in the <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">0</code> to <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">2^{size}-1</code> interval.</li></ul><ul><li><code>nsw</code>: no signed wrap: the operation is partial, i.e. fails if the sum of the two operands (interpreted as signed numbers) is not in the <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">-2^{size-1}</code> to<code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">2^{size-1} - 1</code> interval.</li></ul><ul><li><code>nusw</code>: no unsigned plus signed wrap: the addition of the first operand (interpreted as an unsigned number) and the second one (interpreted as a signed number) fails if its value is not in the <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">0</code> to <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">2^{size}-1</code> interval. This is useful when doing pointer arithmetic (address (unsigned) + offset (signed))</li></ul><p>Note that the simultaneous combination of different flags may be unimplemented (as it never happens in practice).</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bisub\"><a href=\"#val-bisub\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bisub : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">flags</span>:<a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Flags/Biadd/index.html#type-t\">Operator.Flags.Biadd.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector Integer SUBtraction. See <a href=\"#val-biadd\"><code>biadd</code></a> for the flag meanings</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bimul\"><a href=\"#val-bimul\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bimul : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">flags</span>:<a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Flags/Bimul/index.html#type-t\">Operator.Flags.Bimul.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector Integer MULtiplication. See <a href=\"#val-biadd\"><code>biadd</code></a> for the flag meanings</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bshl\"><a href=\"#val-bshl\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bshl : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">flags</span>:<a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Flags/Bshl/index.html#type-t\">Operator.Flags.Bshl.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector SHift Left, If second argument is larger than size, bshl returns 0.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bashr\"><a href=\"#val-bashr\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bashr : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Arithmetic shift right: fill with the most significant bit.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-blshr\"><a href=\"#val-blshr\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> blshr : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Logical shift right: fill with 0.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-beq\"><a href=\"#val-beq\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> beq : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-boolean\">boolean</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector equality</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bisle\"><a href=\"#val-bisle\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bisle : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-boolean\">boolean</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Signed comparison between two bitvectors (using less-or-equal <code>&lt;=</code>). Bitvectors are interpreted as integers in <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">[-2^{size-1}..-2^{size-1}-1]</code> using two's complement.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-biule\"><a href=\"#val-biule\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> biule : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-boolean\">boolean</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Unsigned comparison between two bitvectors (using less-or-equal <code>&lt;=</code>). Bitvectors are interpreted as positive integers in <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">[0..-2^{size}-1]</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bconcat\"><a href=\"#val-bconcat\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bconcat : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size1</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size2</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector concatenation: the new bitvector's size is the sum of the sizes of the arguments. The first argument becomes the most significant bits.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bextract\"><a href=\"#val-bextract\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bextract : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">index</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">oldsize</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar1\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar1</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Extract a <code>size</code> of a bitvector of total size <code>oldsize</code>, starting at <code>index</code>. Should satisfy <code>index + size &lt;= oldsize</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-band\"><a href=\"#val-band\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> band : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector bitwise and</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bor\"><a href=\"#val-bor\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bor : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector bitwise or</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bxor\"><a href=\"#val-bxor\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bxor : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector bitwise xor</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-buext\"><a href=\"#val-buext\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> buext : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">oldsize</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar1\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar1</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Unsingned-extend (pad left with zero) the argument bitvector until it reaches the specified <code>size</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bsext\"><a href=\"#val-bsext\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bsext : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">oldsize</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar1\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar1</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Sign-extend (pad left with topbit) the argument bitvector until it reaches the specified <code>size</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bisdiv\"><a href=\"#val-bisdiv\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bisdiv : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector signed division (truncate towards 0)</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bismod\"><a href=\"#val-bismod\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bismod : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector signed modulo: should satisfy <code>a = b*(bisdiv a b) + bismod a b</code>, just like C-modulo. This means it can be negative for negative divisions.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-biudiv\"><a href=\"#val-biudiv\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> biudiv : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector unsigned division (corresponds to euclidian division)</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-biumod\"><a href=\"#val-biumod\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> biumod : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector unsigned modulo (corresponds to euclidian remainder)</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bofbool\"><a href=\"#val-bofbool\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bofbool : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-boolean\">boolean</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar1\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar1</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Turn a boolean into a bitvector of the given <code>size</code>: <code>false</code> is <code>0</code> and <code>true</code> is <code>1</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-valid\"><a href=\"#val-valid\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> valid : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Operator__.Operator_sig.access_type</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-boolean\">boolean</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar1\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar1</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Returns true if the access to the pointer in memory is valid.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-valid_ptr_arith\"><a href=\"#val-valid_ptr_arith\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> valid_ptr_arith : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Operator__.Operator_sig.arith_type</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-boolean\">boolean</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>valid_ptr_arith(ptr,off)</code> where <code>ptr</code> is a pointer (unsigned) and <code>off</code> a signed integer offset returns <code>true</code> if <code>ptr + off</code> (or <code>ptr - off</code>, depending on the <code>arith_type</code>) is in-bound.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bshift\"><a href=\"#val-bshift\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bshift : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">offset</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">max</span>:<span>int option</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar1\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar1</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>bshift ptr ~offset</code> returns <code>ptr + offset</code>. If <code>max</code> is not None, limits further pointer arithmetics: one cannot go beyond max. Note: offset and max are in bytes, not in bits.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bindex\"><a href=\"#val-bindex\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bindex : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span>int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>bindex</code> takes an integer <code>k</code> and two binary values <code>ptr</code> and <code>off</code>. It returns <code>ptr + k*off</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bchoose\"><a href=\"#val-bchoose\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bchoose : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span>int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>, <a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar1\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar1</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>If s is a set, and c is a &quot;choice&quot; (i.e. valuation of conditions), choose an element of set according to choice.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-biconst\"><a href=\"#val-biconst\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> biconst : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Z</span>.t <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar0\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar0</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Binary constant with given size and value</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-buninit\"><a href=\"#val-buninit\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> buninit : <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><a href=\"#type-binary\">binary</a> <a href=\"../../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar0\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar0</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Uninitialized binary value</p></div></div></details></div>"}